Mem_description: The sprightly manner in which the Takacs played the first movement brought to mind a specific memory. My wife and I were walking on a hillside in the Adivondad region of NY State when we came upon a swarm of dragon flies flying around each other in a sunny spot. There were dozens of them, never leaving that sunny spot for as long as we gazed at them. All the same species. They seemed to be enjoying each other.
Story_description: The death scene from Romeo and Juliette, which I have heard Beethoven had in mind when he wrote this movement. The music perfectly fits this scene, so it is not difficult to imagine it during this movement.
Other_info: The last movement of the Hough had a very striking musical depiction of laughter, among the best I have heard from any composer.

Mem_description: First falling in love with Beethoven's string quartet because of a film. I was making at the time, in 2022 -- 14th string quartet was my first love -- worked backwards -- wrote the film in March of 2022 with thoughts of summer -- this movement, while not in the film, exhibited the character or expression I wished to capture -- reminds me of a time filled with hope and excitement at the opportunity to make films, sitting in a cabin in the Pocons snowed in, dreaming of sunnier days
Story_description: Always bad with melody one memory of music, but I took note of a film I'd like to make, about two sisters figuring out a way to convince their father to rejoin the living after becoming a recluse following the death of his wife, their mother. The scene is tense because the younger sister, who lives with the father, is less optimistic than the older sister, who feels like she has all the answers (she doesn't, which she will soon find out).
Other_info: I'm excited to re-experience the Hough string quartet, as this was my first experience.

Mem_description: I kept seeing the mundane, less commercial streets of Paris that I remembered from when I went there with my family 14 years ago... I remembered light gray, cobblestone alternating with pavement, clean and neat. Fall light: a dull but lovely golden afternoon/early evening sunlight through moody november clouds. I remember absolutely no person but the streets, the streets between various tiny parks in the city, and somehow green trees - not too tall, thin bodies.
Story_description: Influenced by Vikram Seth's An Equal Music perhaps, the novel, I imagined I was part of a string quartet, auditioning for one whoae members are already old. I only imagined the fictional anticipation, excitement, hope.

Mem_description:
It brought back my visits to Paris, the restaurants, (as an accumulation of the previous pieces) and the people I met. The Barnhart’s escargot. 
But it is also connected with the waving trees in the park Luxembourg.
Story_description: The first movement signals an opening of a season, it could be fictional then it is also based on experiences, and earlier exposure to this piece.  The scene was about low rolling hills, no trees, no animals and I was there, alone, owning the space and the fleeting time
Other_info: The great composer and the musicians connect the scenes into a big picture.  In part my imaginings were the expressions of the musicians who were able to connect me to the composer’s mind. An effect not possible listening to some streaming or even watching a video.  In fact it was about the listener “being seen”.
